  stimulus_text = 'The novel *The Great Gatsby* by F. Scott Fitzgerald is one of the most famous works of American literature. Its themes of love, loss, and the American Dream have resonated with readers for generations. The novel''s central character, Jay Gatsby, is a self-made millionaire who throws lavish parties in the hopes of winning back his former love, Daisy Buchanan. However, Gatsby''s pursuit of Daisy is ultimately futile, as he is unable to escape his past and the social barriers that divide him from her. Fitzgerald''s use of symbolism and imagery in the novel help to underscore the novel''s powerful themes.',
